I created a terrible misunderstanding by oversharing unecessary intimate details with a girl I was crazy about which crossed her boundaries and she decided that we should stop talking. We did, going through the guilt was very difficult, though a week later she sent me a few farewell messages to relieve the situation and I suggested trying again. We talked for two more days and I tried to get back to _all that we had,_ but she reminded me that I _broke her first,_ so it was no longer the same. He told me to commit suicide and when I asked to meet up with him, he kept making excuses. My friends knew rhat something was off with him, but I refused to believe it. In July 2020, after three months together, that;s when I found out. I got a message saying that we should break up because he left his phone at his mate's house for three months. I said "That's absolutely ridiculous!" That's when I asked one of his mates, who told me that him and his mates were doing it for a prank. I messaged my "boyfriend" and broke up with him. I told him exactly what I thought of him and he got suspended at school because my friends took pictures of our conversations and showed it to the headteacher. When he went mad at me and said that I hurt him, I said "I don't care how bad it hurts, because you broke me first!"  Present day - We get along now. He came out as gay to me and I came out as Omnisexual and Non Binary to him. We don't talk about what happened that day anymore. We aren't exactly friends, but he's a much better person now. We graduated high school a couple of weeks ago. He's off to college and I'm going to Sixth Form. We're going to keep in touch. I still haven't forgiven him for what he did, but I gave him a second chance, since he promised to change himself.
